# Tailwind CSS Rules

## CRITICAL: No CSS Outside CSS Files

### Forbidden Practices

```vue
<!-- ❌ ABSOLUTELY FORBIDDEN - Style blocks in Vue components -->
<style scoped>
.button { color: red; }
</style>

<!-- ❌ FORBIDDEN - Inline styles -->
<button style="color: red; padding: 10px;">Click</button>

<!-- ❌ FORBIDDEN - CSS-in-JS -->
const styles = { color: 'red' }
```

### Correct Approach

```vue
<!-- ✅ CORRECT - Tailwind utility classes -->
<button class="text-red-500 px-4 py-2 rounded hover:bg-red-100">
  Click
</button>

<!-- ✅ CORRECT - If custom CSS absolutely needed, add to src/assets/main.css -->
```

## Tailwind Best Practices

### Responsive Design (Mobile-First)

```html
<!-- Base styles apply to mobile, then scale up -->
<div class="
  w-full           <!-- Mobile: full width -->
  md:w-1/2         <!-- Tablet: half width -->
  lg:w-1/3         <!-- Desktop: third width -->
  xl:w-1/4         <!-- Large: quarter width -->
">

<!-- Common breakpoints -->
<!-- sm: 640px, md: 768px, lg: 1024px, xl: 1280px, 2xl: 1536px -->
```

### State Variants

```html
<!-- Hover, focus, active states -->
<button class="
  bg-blue-500
  hover:bg-blue-600
  focus:ring-2
  focus:ring-blue-300
  active:bg-blue-700
  disabled:opacity-50
  disabled:cursor-not-allowed
">

<!-- Group hover -->
<div class="group">
  <span class="group-hover:text-blue-500">Hover parent to change me</span>
</div>
```

### Dark Mode

```html
<!-- Dark mode variants -->
<div class="
  bg-white dark:bg-gray-800
  text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100
  border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700
">
```

### RTL Support

```html
<!-- RTL-aware spacing and positioning -->
<div class="
  mr-4 rtl:mr-0 rtl:ml-4
  text-left rtl:text-right
  pl-2 rtl:pl-0 rtl:pr-2
">

<!-- Or use logical properties -->
<div class="
  ms-4          <!-- margin-inline-start -->
  me-4          <!-- margin-inline-end -->
  ps-2          <!-- padding-inline-start -->
  pe-2          <!-- padding-inline-end -->
  text-start    <!-- text-align: start -->
  text-end      <!-- text-align: end -->
">
```

