## Spacing Consistency

Use consistent spacing scale:
- `gap-2` / `p-2` / `m-2` = 8px
- `gap-4` / `p-4` / `m-4` = 16px
- `gap-6` / `p-6` / `m-6` = 24px
- `gap-8` / `p-8` / `m-8` = 32px

## Custom CSS (Only in src/assets/main.css)

If you absolutely need custom CSS, add it to `src/assets/main.css`:

```css
/* src/assets/main.css */
@import 'tailwindcss';

/* Custom CSS only when Tailwind can't achieve the effect */
@layer components {
  .btn-gradient {
    @apply bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-500 to-purple-600 text-white;
  }
}

@layer utilities {
  .text-shadow {
    text-shadow: 2px 2px 4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
  }
}
```

## Extract Repeated Patterns to Components

Instead of creating CSS classes, create Vue components:

```vue
<!-- ✅ CORRECT - Create reusable component -->
<!-- components/ui/Button.vue -->
<script setup lang="ts">
interface Props {
  variant?: 'primary' | 'secondary' | 'danger'
  size?: 'sm' | 'md' | 'lg'
}
const props = withDefaults(defineProps<Props>(), {
  variant: 'primary',
  size: 'md'
})

const classes = computed(() => ({
  'px-3 py-1.5 text-sm': props.size === 'sm',
  'px-4 py-2 text-base': props.size === 'md',
  'px-6 py-3 text-lg': props.size === 'lg',
  'bg-blue-600 text-white hover:bg-blue-700': props.variant === 'primary',
  'bg-gray-200 text-gray-800 hover:bg-gray-300': props.variant === 'secondary',
  'bg-red-600 text-white hover:bg-red-700': props.variant === 'danger',
}))
</script>

<template>
  <button :class="['rounded-lg transition-colors', classes]">
    <slot />
  </button>
</template>

<!-- Usage -->
<BaseButton variant="primary" size="lg">Submit</BaseButton>
```
